This document describes how to install the OpenNSL software provided in
this package on the Agema AG9032v1 switch.

Pre-requisites:  The switch must have ONL(Open Network Linux) installed via ONIE.
    Must log in as user root, password is onl
    All commands run as root user.

Downloading and running OpenNSL
============================================================
* download the OpenNSL-1.0 .deb package
    root@localhost:~# tftp IPaddress
    tftp> binary
    tftp> get OpenNSL-1.0.deb
    tftp> quit
   
* Install the OpenNSL-1.0.deb package
    root@localhost:~# dpkg -i OpenNSL-1.0.deb

    Note:  It may be necessary to run the following command before installing
           OpenNSL because sometimes the ONIE install leaves some packages
           in a half-configured state:

           dpkg --configure -a

* Insert kernel modules, then the switch will be ready to run one of the examples. 
    root@localhost:~# chmod 777 insmod.sh
    root@localhost:~# ./insmod.sh
    root@localhost:~# ./example_drivshell


* Breakout to 100G or 25 configuration
    root@localhost:~# cd /etc/opennsl
    root@localhost:~# cp -af opennsl_100G.cfg opennsl.cfg    //for breakout to 100G
    root@localhost:~# cp -af opennsl_25G.cfg opennsl.cfg     //for breakout to 25G
    root@localhost:~# cd - && ./example_drivshell

